Already, the WRC Safari Rally has appointed a Covid-19 compliance officer with regular tests scheduled for anyone working for both the Equator Rally and the Safari and safe zones created at the Service Park at Naivasha’s Kenya Wildlife Service Training Institute.The Service Park will be used for both the Equator Rally and the Safari. The Kenya Motor Sports Federation (KMSF) is this week expected to make an announcement on the way forward for next month’s Equator Rally following the government’s directive on Friday suspending all sporting activities to help contain the coronavirus. 



