The Service Park will be used for both the Equator Rally and the Safari. 

For the WRC Safari Rally, after the ceremonial start from the Kenyatta International Conference Centre, the cars will head to the Moi International Sports Centre for the Super Special Stage before hitting the transport section to Naivasha where the main action will be based.   

Already, foreign crews from as far as South Africa, Zambia and Zimbabwe have transported their competition cars and service parts ahead of the Equator Rally which will have added importance as it will be a dry run for the WRC Safari Rally both for competitors and organisers. 

Motorsports, like all other sporting events, was suspended in March last year by the government to contain the spread of the coronavirus with rally action resuming early this year with the opening KNRC round in Nakuru.  

KMSF is the national motorsports governing body mandated to oversee rallying, autocross, karting, and hill climb events by the government and the International Motorsport Federation. Bengi, Tejveer to lead others off in Machakos. After Machakos, the next event will be the Equator Rally. Health ministry says the death toll is now 2,117, the cases 130,214 and the positivity rate 16.4 per cent.
